them and bring them into the future.

01:12:55.560 --> 01:12:59.900
More folklorists need
to get on IRBs.

01:12:59.900 --> 01:13:03.640
I have done a lot of work
trying to educate IRB members

01:13:03.640 --> 01:13:06.820
around the country on
qualitative research.

01:13:06.820 --> 01:13:09.300
Just getting the means
to things like the idea

01:13:09.300 --> 01:13:13.320
that you can't always give the
IRB your exact list of questions

01:13:13.320 --> 01:13:15.080
because there's going
to be followup questions

01:13:15.080 --> 01:13:16.820
that you don't know what
they're going to be yet.

01:13:16.820 --> 01:13:21.050
That interviews in folklore are
never completely structured.

01:13:21.050 --> 01:13:22.980
They're always somewhat
semistructured

01:13:22.980 --> 01:13:26.050
and informal to some extent.

01:13:26.050 --> 01:13:32.810
The more folklorists get in there
and become a part of that board,

01:13:32.810 --> 01:13:34.890
the better they can make life

01:13:34.890 --> 01:13:37.840
for other qualitative
researchers at their institutions.

01:13:37.840 --> 01:13:42.810
IRBs are so different
at every university.

01:13:42.810 --> 01:13:46.750
My university has a wonderful IRB
with lots of qualitative people

01:13:46.750 --> 01:13:49.840
on it and very flexible
open minded people.

01:13:49.840 --> 01:13:52.000
That's not the case
at every university.

01:13:52.000 --> 01:13:55.690
And it's really not fair because
the folklorist has a great project

01:13:55.690 --> 01:13:57.430
that would be highly encouraged

01:13:57.430 --> 01:14:00.450
at Bowling Green State
University might run into a wall

01:14:00.450 --> 01:14:04.530 position:56%
at another place just because the
IRB is stuck in a different mindset.

01:14:04.530 --> 01:14:08.360
So, that's why it's so important
for more of us to not be so afraid

01:14:08.360 --> 01:14:10.320
of the IRB but, you know,
you can't beat them,

01:14:10.320 --> 01:14:12.350
so join them and change them.

01:14:12.350 --> 01:14:14.600
And with the digital
culture, in the same way,

01:14:14.600 --> 01:14:16.380
bring them into the present

01:14:16.380 --> 01:14:20.050
because many IRB members have no
interest in learning about it.

01:14:20.050 --> 01:14:23.460
Let alone, making their right
decisions about researchers

01:14:23.460 --> 01:14:25.900
who are doing their research there.

01:14:25.900 --> 01:14:27.200
&gt;&gt; Andrea Kitta: Yeah.

01:14:27.200 --> 01:14:30.090
I've had similar experiences
where I--

01:14:30.090 --> 01:14:32.130
I'm not going to say anything
bad about our IRB board

01:14:32.130 --> 01:14:36.560
but things have gotten
caught up for very silly to--

01:14:36.560 --> 01:14:38.220
at least to a folklorist reasons.

01:14:38.220 --> 01:14:40.680
