I get tagged a lot

01:14:43.910 --> 01:14:47.130
for not knowing exactly how
many participants I'll have,

01:14:47.130 --> 01:14:48.430
which is something I can't know

01:14:48.430 --> 01:14:50.260
until I start actually
doing the research.

01:14:50.260 --> 01:14:53.750
But they-- I've gotten held up
for months at a time, you know,

01:14:53.750 --> 01:14:58.010
and had issues based on things
that are very minor compared

01:14:58.010 --> 01:15:01.480
to the major, you know,
ethical issues I'm seeing,

01:15:01.480 --> 01:15:04.360
they're more worried about,
you know, number of people,

01:15:04.360 --> 01:15:06.880
number of questions,
those kinds of things.

01:15:06.880 --> 01:15:08.180
So, it is very true.

01:15:08.180 --> 01:15:12.410 position:56%
A lot of these boards either tend
towards, you know, looking at people

01:15:12.410 --> 01:15:13.710
who maybe are a little
more out of touch,

01:15:13.710 --> 01:15:16.500
with what current researches is
kind of happening or they tend

01:15:16.500 --> 01:15:19.000
to be highly medical
and are looking more at,

01:15:19.000 --> 01:15:20.640
you know, are you drawing blood.

01:15:20.640 --> 01:15:24.890
Are you-- and I don't quite
understand, you know--

01:15:24.890 --> 01:15:27.330
in some cases too, I've had people
say, oh we are just asking people

01:15:27.330 --> 01:15:29.200
for stories that can't
possibly harm anybody.

01:15:29.200 --> 01:15:30.500
And I'm like, well, no, it could.

01:15:30.500 --> 01:15:31.800
&gt;&gt; Montana Miller: It could, yeah.

01:15:31.800 --> 01:15:33.100
&gt;&gt; Andrea Kitta: Yeah,
absolutely could.

01:15:33.100 --> 01:15:35.830
So it is-- it's very-- very
much depends like especially

01:15:35.830 --> 01:15:38.280
on the organization,
the institution.

01:15:38.280 --> 01:15:39.620
&gt;&gt; Montana Miller: But
something encouraging is

01:15:39.620 --> 01:15:42.130
that if there's a board
