the shelves and unused.

02:59:01.350 --> 02:59:06.370
Even if they've been digitized,
they're very, relatively speaking,

02:59:06.370 --> 02:59:08.550
unused and still rather obscure.

02:59:08.550 --> 02:59:10.220
And that's not why we
went into this business.

02:59:10.220 --> 02:59:12.140
We went into this business
to document not

02:59:12.140 --> 02:59:15.450 position:56%
for obscurity but for impact, right.

02:59:15.450 --> 02:59:19.990
To put these individual stories
to document these cultures.

02:59:19.990 --> 02:59:25.740
So that said, AV archives, all
of AV archives has the problem

02:59:25.740 --> 02:59:29.030
of discovery and usability, right.

02:59:29.030 --> 02:59:30.330
It's time-based media.

02:59:30.330 --> 02:59:31.630
It takes time to use.

02:59:31.630 --> 02:59:36.850
We have a complete reliance
on texts in this model.

02:59:36.850 --> 02:59:39.540
Text enables discovery really.

02:59:39.540 --> 02:59:41.500
There was a point in
oral history's history

02:59:41.500 --> 02:59:44.120
where it was actually
seen as the only outcome.

02:59:44.120 --> 02:59:47.950
