&gt;&gt; Alan: No, I can talk softly.

03:18:43.570 --> 03:18:46.710
Could you just talk through exactly

03:18:46.710 --> 03:18:50.480
like if I give you a
tape, what would you do?

03:18:50.480 --> 03:18:52.440
What you-- Is there a--
Do you use Dragon Speak

03:18:52.440 --> 03:18:54.490 position:56%
or something to recognize the words?

03:18:54.490 --> 03:18:55.790
&gt;&gt; Doug Boyd: Right.

03:18:55.790 --> 03:18:57.750
So we're not actively formally
using speech recognition.

03:18:57.750 --> 03:19:01.670
First, we digitize the tape, in
accordance with best practices

03:19:01.670 --> 03:19:03.550
and we'd accession that tape.

03:19:03.550 --> 03:19:07.110 position:56%
But at that point, let's say you
just had a name written on that tape

03:19:07.110 --> 03:19:08.410
and we didn't know
anything about it.

03:19:08.410 --> 03:19:11.300
Maybe we knew it was part of a
civil rights project, that's it.

03:19:11.300 --> 03:19:12.600
That's all we know.

03:19:12.600 --> 03:19:17.440
So, at that point, we'd-- you know,
if it fell into the queue of things

03:19:17.440 --> 03:19:20.500
that we were going to put
online, it would go there

03:19:20.500 --> 03:19:22.050
and we would index that interview.

03:19:22.050 --> 03:19:23.480
So somebody would listen
to that interview,

03:19:23.480 --> 03:19:25.740
and while they're listening to that
interview, they would be typing

03:19:25.740 --> 03:19:27.580
and they would be tagging
those moments.

03:19:27.580 --> 03:19:32.000
This is a major subject
transition tag and start typing,

03:19:32.000 --> 03:19:34.910
and then rather than transcribe,
because we really don't know what's

03:19:34.910 --> 03:19:38.410
in there and I can't afford to
transcribe everything we bring in.

03:19:38.410 --> 03:19:42.260
And so at that point, we get a good
sense for what's in that interview,

03:19:42.260 --> 03:19:44.570
then we'd make the-- then we'd
actually write the description

03:19:44.570 --> 03:19:46.950
of the interview because
now we know what it's about.

03:19:46.950 --> 03:19:50.400
And then we'd actually make that
decision, do we press the button

03:19:50.400 --> 03:19:54.790
and make it go live to the
internet or not at that point.

03:19:54.790 --> 03:19:59.140
It's a good question.

